---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import effect from "@/assets/images/science/pfasEffect.png";
---

<Layout>
  <section class="pfas-section">
    <article class="pfas-article">
      <h2 class="pfas-title">Have You Heard of PFAS?</h2>
      <p>
        You’ve probably never heard that word before… but have you ever used
        non-stick pans with Teflon? Well, you might be surprised to know that <strong
          >“Teflon” contains some very dangerous chemicals called PFAS</strong
        >, which <strong>don’t break down easily</strong> and can stay in the environment
        <strong>forever</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>
        But that’s not all — these substances <strong
          >can get into our bodies</strong
        > and cause serious health problems like:
        <strong>cancer, infertility, high cholesterol, thyroid issues</strong>,
        and more.
      </p>
      <p>
        And it’s not just pots and pans. PFAS are found in all kinds of everyday
        products, like:
      </p>
      <ul class="pfas-list">
        <li>Waterproof clothing</li>
        <li>Food packaging (like microwave popcorn bags)</li>
        <li>Long-lasting makeup</li>
        <li>Cleaning and personal care products</li>
        <li>And many more!</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <strong>So how do PFAS get into the environment?</strong> When industries
        make these products, they often use PFAS — and <strong
          >many don’t properly treat their wastewater</strong
        >. That means these toxic substances end up in our rivers, soil, crops,
        and even the air we breathe.
      </p>
      <p>
        What’s worse is that <strong
          >water treatment plants can’t remove PFAS</strong
        >, because they’re so resistant.
      </p>
      <strong class="pfas-warning">PFAS pollution is growing every day.</strong>
    </article>
    <Image src={effect} alt="PFAS environment effects" />

    <article class="pfas-article">
      <h2 class="pfas-title">What am I doing about it?</h2>
      <p>
        In my research, I’m working on a solution to remove PFAS from water
        using <strong>electricity</strong>
        and <strong>special materials</strong> that help break these substances down.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="pfas-article">
      <h2 class="pfas-title">What can you do?</h2>
      <ul class="pfas-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Learn more and change your consumption habits</strong>. Avoid
          products with PFAS when you can.
        </li>
        <li>
          Read labels — look for <strong>“PFAS-free”</strong> or more natural options.
        </li>
        <li>
          Share this info with family and friends. <strong
            >Together, we can make a difference.</strong
          >
        </li>
      </ul>
      <strong class="pfas-cta"
        >Protecting our health and the planet is in our hands.</strong
      >
    </article>
  </section>
</Layout>
<style>
  img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    object-fit: cover;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    margin-block: var(--fs-m);
    border-radius: 1rem;
  }
  p {
    margin-inline-start: var(--fs-s);
  }
  ul {
    margin-inline-start: var(--fs-m);
  }
  strong {
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: var(--fs-s);
  }
  .pfas-section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    padding: var(--fs-m);
    max-width: 1240px;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .pfas-title {
    font-size: var(--fs-m);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: var(--fs-s);
  }

  .pfas-list {
    list-style-type: disc;
    padding-left: 2rem;
    margin-block: var(--fs-s);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .pfas-list li {
    font-size: var(--fs-s);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .pfas-warning {
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .pfas-cta {
    display: block;
    margin-top: var(--fs-s);
    font-size: var(--fs-s);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
